1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,350
Man has to seek God in error and forgetfulness and foolishness.

2
00:00:04,300 --> 00:00:08,762
For deity has in it the power of all things and no thing has the like.

3
00:00:08,762 --> 00:00:13,000
The sovran light of the impartible essence illumines all things.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,825
St Dionysius says that beauty is good order with pre-eminent lucidity.

5
00:00:17,825 --> 00:00:21,025
Thus God is an arrangement of three Persons.

6
00:00:21,025 --> 00:00:38,050
And the soul’s lower powers should be ordered to her higher and her higher ones to God; her outward senses to her inward and her inward ones to reason; thought to intuition and intuition to the will and all to unity, so that the soul may be alone with nothing flowing into her but sheer divinity, flowing here into itself.

7
00:00:38,050 --> 00:00:45,375
As St Dionysius says, By purity she has discovered her capacity and only her superior powers are in operation.

8
00:00:45,532 --> 00:00:53,019
It has been said by one philosopher that as soon as the chief power takes command the others all run into it, leaving their own work.

9
00:00:52,969 --> 00:01:00,069
Then the soul is in order and in her pure nature, i.e. in her supernal light-nature wherein all things are potential.

10
00:01:00,069 --> 00:01:04,569
A heathen doctor says, If the soul knew herself she would know all things.

11
00:01:04,569 --> 00:01:21,357
Deity flowed into the Father and into the Son and into the Holy Ghost: in eternity into itself and in time into creatures, to each as much as it can hold: to the stone its being, to the tree its growth, to beasts sensation, to the angels reason and to mankind all these four natures.

12
00:01:21,357 --> 00:01:29,357
When God was made man he took upon himself by grace, in time, the nature of all things, which in eternity was his by nature.

13
00:01:29,357 --> 00:01:32,919
As St Paul says, ‘To me Christ is all things.

14
00:01:32,919 --> 00:01:36,819
Here it was a matter of the light and reflection of his own nature.

15
00:01:36,819 --> 00:01:41,782
God’s being is fontal: flowing and fixed, final as well as the first.

16
00:01:41,782 --> 00:01:44,619
From being power flows out into work.

17
00:01:44,619 --> 00:01:52,457
In this sense the three Persons are the storehouse of divinity and the three Persons are poured forth into the essence of the soul as grace.

18
00:01:52,457 --> 00:01:58,419
God’s being in the essence of the soul is the imitation of the Persons and one being permeates the other.

19
00:01:58,419 --> 00:02:04,294
Her chief power flows from the essence of the soul just as the three Persons issue from the Godhead.

20
00:02:04,294 --> 00:02:09,332
And when God pours his grace into the soul it is into her essence that he pours it.

21
00:02:09,332 --> 00:02:14,507
For into the soul’s essence no speck can ever fall, do her powers what they may.

22
00:02:14,507 --> 00:02:23,869
The chief power of the soul draws its virtue from the grace existing in the essence of the soul and this highest power goes out into the lower ones, into their essence.

23
00:02:23,869 --> 00:02:30,869
The crescent soul, the spirit receptive of God’s nature, is the imitation of Christ’s Person and man’s nature.

24
00:02:30,869 --> 00:02:41,182
The soul when she reaches divine nature is deprived of all deficiency and imperfection; she suffers death in divine nature, getting God’s nature in herself as the Father does in him.

25
00:02:41,182 --> 00:02:52,882
She takes it not from her own nature, she receives it from God’s nature into her nature; she receives perfection and power according to the words of St Paul, ‘I can do all things in him that strengtheneth me.

26
00:02:52,882 --> 00:02:59,982
The wisdom thence arising in her mind begins in understanding and is perfected in will and it has neither heart nor thought.

27
00:02:59,982 --> 00:03:11,894
St Dionysius says, As the soul takes the outgoing tide to journey in eternity and time and in her own intelligence, so on the ebb does she return; as God the soul flows back again, without exertion.

28
00:03:11,894 --> 00:03:16,644
God returns to himself as little mindful of his own as though they were not.

29
00:03:16,644 --> 00:03:18,732
And the soul shall do the same.

30
00:03:18,732 --> 00:03:37,094
She shall grasp with her manhood the Person of the Son, and with the Person of the Son she shall apprehend the Father and the Holy Ghost in both, and them both in the Holy Ghost; and with the Person of the Father she shall apprehend his simple essence, and with the essence the abyss, and shall sink into the void without matter and without form.

31
00:03:37,094 --> 00:03:43,519
Matter and form, being all knowledge, she loses in this unity, for she herself has come to naught.

32
00:03:43,519 --> 00:03:52,869
God does all her work, he preserves her in his being and leads her in his power into his very Godhead where she flows with deity itself into all God flows into.

33
00:03:52,869 --> 00:03:56,307
She is all things’ place and has herself no place.

34
00:03:56,307 --> 00:04:00,569
This is the most eternal wisdom, which has neither heart nor thought.

35
00:04:00,569 --> 00:04:08,069
So nigh soul flows to God that many are deceived; but what she is she is by grace, and where she is she is by another’s power.

36
00:04:08,069 --> 00:04:16,457
Yet she approaches near enough to God to be, in the power of the Father, invested with divinity by grace the same as the Father is by nature.

37
00:04:16,457 --> 00:04:26,107
St Paul says: ‘In the same image we shall go from one glory to another,’ meaning, we shall receive divinity in its perfection and all that is consequent thereon.

38
00:04:26,107 --> 00:04:34,294
Therein she shall conceive divinity as it conceives itself and her will and God’s will shall be one: whatever God may be we shall be with God.

39
00:04:34,294 --> 00:04:42,857
No one can attain it in this body, but when God gives the soul his final gift, the vision of his Godhead, the soul is raised up in the Trinity.

40
00:04:42,857 --> 00:04:45,682
May we attain to this, So help us

41
00:04:45,844 --> 00:04:46,681
God.

42
00:04:46,631 --> 00:04:47,556
Amen.

